race.comment: SHANGRI LA BOY (2) used his tactical speed to advantage when jumping in trip for a slick win over 1800m in the G3 Gloaming Stakes at Rosehill. Goes to a new pain threshold today and gets an even better set-up from the draw. Hard to catch. ATTICA (1) exciting colt who was set a massive task when circling the field for a comprehensive victory from last on the turn in the LR Dulcify 3YO Quality Hcp over the mile here. Has a stack of upside and since fitted with a 1200m tick-over trial. Will be surging late. WITHIN THE LAW (11) the barrier gods have been unkind again and she backs up quickly. No match for the tough WFA opposition when a fading ninth over 1609m in the G1 King Charles III Stakes at this track last Saturday. Collett back on and stays in the mix. CHAMPAGNE HERO (7) shuffled back early and never got a clear crack at them in the straight when seventh in the G3 Gloaming. Has further improvement to come and don't underestimate. SAN GIOVANNI (3) strips fitter from the good draw.
